The paper discusses interpretability of blackbox machine learning models, which is a common topic in the fields of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of deep learning models and GANs suggests a focus on computer vision (cs.CV) and generative models (cs.GM). The evaluation of the approaches on a blackbox model trained on public datasets suggests a focus on cybersecurity (cs.CR) or software engineering (cs.SE).
